section.text:

          Subpart III of part D of title III of the
			 Public Health Service Act (
            42 U.S.C. 254l et seq.
          ) is amended by adding at the
			 end the following:

subparagraph.text:
maintain a
				minimum level of academic standing during the period of the scholarship, as
				determined by the Secretary;

clause.text:
a
				health professional shortage area (as defined by the National Health Service
				Corps under section 332);

paragraph.text:
data on any
				changes in health professional shortage areas or medically underserved areas
				within the State;

the number of
				additional full-time physicians that would be required to eliminate such health
				professional shortage areas or medically underserved areas in the State;

the number of
				individuals who received a scholarship but failed to comply with its
				requirements;

the action taken
				by the State to recoup scholarship funds in the case of any non-compliance;
				and

how documentation
			 requirements designed for paper-based records should be modified for electronic
			 records;

whether or not
			 the documentation requirements are overly burdensome on physicians and detract
			 from patient care;

the
			 administrative costs to physician practices of the current documentation
			 requirements;
